Exercise 01 — GDB Basics
==========================

The binary runs and prints nothing useful.
Somewhere inside it, a function called success() prints the flag.
It is never called in the normal control flow.

Your goal: use GDB to call success() directly.

  Load the binary in GDB:
    gdb ./target

  List all functions in the binary:
    info functions

  Call success() without running the program normally:
    call (void) success()

  Or: set a breakpoint, run, then jump to it:
    break main
    run
    jump success

Call success() to reveal the flag, then submit it: horizon done HRZ{...}
